text: The first film (despite how awesome it is) is a product of it's time in the way that it feels very early 2000's and hasn't aged beyond that. This film is one of these action films that is fun because it's unrealistic just like ("Fast and Furious 4"* - "Fast 8"). I love action film's like these despite how much I'm anti most PG-13 action films (exceptions such as the Nolan Trilogy of Batman movies, most MCU movies, "The Fast and the Furious", "Pirates of the Caribbean", the "Bourne" films, ect.) this looks like a fun film even though they have most likely made it a complete CGI fest. There have been great action films that have CGI but that don't get ruined by it so hopefully this will be the same.    *"Fast & Furious 4" was technically more gritty than fun but the end of the film set the tone for the rest of the franchise. text: What an adrenaline rush this movie is. First things first, if you are going to see this and complain after how unrealistic and over the top it is, then you have completely missed the point. This is what xXx universe brings to the table and that is utterly ridiculous, extreme version of James Bond. Story is unbelievably corny, dialogue is astonishingly stupid and sexist and characters are so cartoonishly stereotypical that you couldn't find them anywhere in the world. But aside all of that,  this was made by someone who knows how to have fun, understands the right approach to this kind of  goofiness and is able to provide us with great stunts although with noticable CGI here and there plus satisfy our neanderthal part of our brain that screams for guns, explosions and  busty babes wrapped around all of that like a perfect present. Vin Diesel pulled it off like there was no 15 year gap between the first and this film and her just solidifies himself as action hero of this era. Do not miss xXx 3 if you just want to turn your brain off and have fun because that is what it goes for, harmless popcorn entertainment and nothing more than  that. 3/5
